 A Chinese firm signed four project investment agreements on a waste-to-energy project with its Bangladeshi partners in Dhaka on Wednesday. According to the agreements, China Machinery Engineering Corporation (CMEC) will set up a 42.5-megawatt waste-to-energy power plant at Aminbazar on the outskirts of Dhaka. According to a project document, the waste to energy power plant has a capacity of 42.5 megawatts and processes around 3,000 tonnes of fresh waste per day collected from the capital area.  Produced by Xinhua Global Service 